{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"76990d66-6cdf-4d10-8b99-10e5196b146b","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Recursive wildcard glob** (Line 9, `EvalHeavy.csproj`) — **High impact**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` forces MSBuild to walk the entire directory tree during evaluation. This is the single most common cause of slow evaluation, especially in repos with `node_modules`, large `obj` folders, or many files. Use a scoped path (e.g., `src\\**\\*.txt`) or a specific extension instead of `*.*`.\n\n### 2. **File I/O via property function** (Line 13, `EvalHeavy.csproj`) — **Medium impact**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n`ReadAllText` performs synchronous disk I/O during evaluation. Property functions that hit the filesystem block the evaluation engine. If the file grows or sits on a slow drive/network share, this directly increases evaluation time. Prefer reading file contents at build-time via a target/task instead.\n\n### 3. **Three-level deep import chain** (`imports/`) — **Low-medium impact**\n```\ncsproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach import adds an XML parse + evaluation pass. Three levels is modest, but it's a pattern that compounds quickly. Flattening or reducing unnecessary nesting helps, especially when multiplied across many projects in a solution.\n\n---\n\n**Recommended priority:** Fix the `**\\*.*` glob first — it dominates evaluation time in most real-world repos. Then move the `ReadAllText` call into a target. The import chain is acceptable at this depth but worth watching as the project grows.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"21d7e694-c352-4d03-9193-7e272a0ee5c4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture of all the files. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":486},"id":"2447c8d9-d68d-470d-8c92-db866b9d0cd2","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:05:13.226Z","parentId":"e95248c8-783d-410a-90fc-af4847afb4c0"}
